data.title: Queen Elisabeth of Romania - "The Poet Queen"
data.meta_description:
Pauline Elisabeth Ottilie Luise zu Wied (29 December 1843 – 2 March 1916) was the Queen consort of Romania as the wife of King Carol I of Romania, widely known by her literary name of Carmen Sylva. (Wiki)
	
	1880s etching by Thiriat, based on a photograph. 
	
	Colouring by me.
